    'Which choice best combines the sentences at the underlined portion so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?',
    'multiple_choice',
    '[{"id":"A","text":"The museum, that will feature works by many artists from around the world, and it will highlight the history of art in the city, will also feature a cafe and a gift shop.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"B","text":"The museum, that will feature works by many artists from around the world, and it will highlight the history of art in the city, will also have a cafe and a gift shop.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"C","text":"The museum, which will feature works by many artists from around the world, and it will highlight the history of art in the city, will also feature a cafe and a gift shop.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"D","text":"The museum, which will feature works by many artists from around the world, and it will highlight the history of art in the city, will also feature a cafe and a gift shop.","is_correct":true,"explanation":""}]'::jsonb,
    'D',
    'Choice D is the best answer because it uses the correct relative pronoun ("which") to introduce a nonrestrictive clause that provides additional information about the museum. The other choices are incorrect because they use the incorrect relative pronoun ("that") or create a comma splice, which is a grammatical error.',
    'Review the passage and eliminate choices that contradict the text.',
    'A new museum is opening in the city. The museum will feature works by many artists from around the world, and it will highlight the history of art in the city. The museum will also feature a cafe and a gift shop.',
