    'What is the main idea of the passage?',
    'multiple_choice',
    '[{"id":"A","text":"The history of the United States is a complex and often contradictory one.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"B","text":"The United States has been a beacon of hope and progress, but it has also been a source of division and conflict.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"C","text":"It is important to be aware of the different perspectives that exist and to be critical of the sources of information that we use.","is_correct":true,"explanation":""},{"id":"D","text":"The most important thing is to be critical of the sources of information that we use.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""}]'::jsonb,
    'C',
    'The passage emphasizes the importance of being aware of different perspectives and being critical of the sources of information.  This is the main idea of the passage.',
    'Review the passage and eliminate choices that contradict the text.',
    'The history of the United States is a complex and often contradictory one.  At times, the country has been a beacon of hope and progress, while at other times, it has been a source of division and conflict.  This is reflected in the many different narratives that have been told about the country’s past, some of which are more accurate than others.  The most important thing is to be aware of the different perspectives that exist and to be critical of the sources of information that we use.',
