    'Which choice best maintains the stylistic consistency of the passage?',
    'multiple_choice',
    '[{"id":"A","text":"The dome of St. Peter’s Basilica, however, was designed by Michelangelo, who was also responsible for the frescoes on the Sistine Chapel ceiling.","is_correct":true,"explanation":""},{"id":"B","text":"The dome of St. Peter''s Basilica, however, was designed by Michelangelo, who was also responsible for the frescoes on the Sistine Chapel ceiling.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"C","text":"The dome of St. Peter’s Basilica, however, was designed by Michelangelo, who is also responsible for the frescoes on the Sistine Chapel ceiling.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""},{"id":"D","text":"The dome of St. Peter’s Basilica, however, was designed by Michelangelo; who was also responsible for the frescoes on the Sistine Chapel ceiling.","is_correct":false,"explanation":""}]'::jsonb,
    'A',
    'The passage uses a mix of past tense and present tense verbs. Since the passage is describing historical events, the past tense is the most appropriate.  The passage is written in a formal tone, so a semicolon should not be used. Choice B is incorrect because it uses a comma splice. Choice C is incorrect because it uses a present tense verb instead of a past tense verb. Choice D is incorrect because it uses a semicolon instead of a comma.',
    'Review the passage and eliminate choices that contradict the text.',
    'The city of Rome is known for its many historic landmarks, and for its beautiful architecture.  In the 16th century, Pope Julius II commissioned the rebuilding of St. Peter’s Basilica, which was a major undertaking, with many artists, architects, and engineers contributing to its construction.   The dome of St. Peter’s Basilica, however, was designed by Michelangelo, who was also responsible for the frescoes on the Sistine Chapel ceiling. The basilica is one of the largest churches in the world, and it is a popular tourist destination.  It''s also a place of worship for many people.',
